 Role Description 
 
The VP of Structured Products is an integral part of the Capital Markets team and will be responsible for the structuring and execution of a variety of asset backed security offerings across asset classes. 
 
Key Responsibilities 
 
 Operational management of securitization transactions and funding 
 Day to day responsibilities and assisting on securitization transactions requiring extensive interaction and coordination of lenders, legal counsel, accounting firms, rating agencies, trustees, servicers and investors. 
 Assist in the preparation, and evaluation of securitization documents. Including all legal and structural matters in conjunction with internal and external legal and the trading desk. 
 Manage existing client relationships and deal teams. 
 Support securitization reporting, waterfall review, and P&L review 
 Interface with various external securitization deal parties including sell-side firms, buy-side accounts, and rating agencies, among others 
 Compliance testing and calculations 
 Vendor and Partner management (review reports and data, document issues, due diligence) 
 
 Qualifications 
 
 5+ years of experience in fixed income structured products 
 Proven experience in the preparation and presentation of summary. And roadshow materials specific to CRE securitizations for rating agencies and investors across both fixed and floating rate multi-borrower transactions, single asset and large loan transactions and agented third party deals. 
 Finance, accounting, economics, or business major 
 Experience analyzing large data sets 
 
 Benefits 
 
 Generous paid time off policy 
 Medical, Dental, Vision Insurance 
 Discretionary bonuses 
